8. Scoring Rubric
Relevance

5 — Directly answers the question with highly relevant content
4 — Mostly on point but with minor redundancy
3 — Partially relevant; misses the core intent
2 — Mostly off-topic
1 — Completely fails to address the question

Completeness

5 — All key information present, nothing missing
4 — Covers main points; minor secondary items missing
3 — Notable gaps in expected content
2 — Severely incomplete
1 — Unusable

Hallucination

Pass — No fabrication; all claims are grounded
Fail — Any key fact is invented, misattributed, or fabricated

